  "doc_id": "49055",
  "text": "This is a pathologic feature composed of fibrous tissue and compressed renal parenchyma, seen frequently in the early stages of a SRM. Although not specific (also seen in some oncocytomas), it has been related to renal cell carcinomas usually small and of low histologic grade, slow growing, and less likely to metastasize [CITATION_1] . Their presence is an indicator of prognostic value [CITATION_2] . This condition allows renal parenchyma-sparing surgery, especially if simple enucleation is considered in patients with multiple tumors, Von Hippel-Lindau disease or familial tendency for RCC.",
